track_notes: This route follows a ridge from the Southeast of the summit to the top. Easy bouldering and bushwhacking, but no clear path. The summit is roomy with enough room to stretch out a 60M dipole.

The drive requires a lifted 4X4. It is necessary to run in 4 low for a few spots. This is a better route than google maps will give because it doesnt run through the North end of Lake Pleasant. The google route will requires scraping through a forest of salt cedar. I lost trim from my Tacoma on the first attempt. I had no issues with this posted route.
track_title: 4X4 drive to park close to summit
